{%- liquid
  assign overline = section.settings.overline
  if overline == blank
    assign overline = 'home.mechanism.overline' | t
  endif
  assign heading = section.settings.heading
  if heading == blank
    assign heading = 'home.mechanism.heading' | t
  endif
  assign subheading = section.settings.subheading
  if subheading == blank
    assign subheading = 'home.mechanism.subheading' | t
  endif
-%}

<section id="how-it-works" class="section-apple nf-mech">
  <div class="apple-container">
    {% render 'section-intro',
      overline: overline,
      heading: heading,
      subheading: subheading,
      theme: 'dark'
    %}
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}
    Scroll-scrubbed stage: the CSS window motif performs the product story —
    window warms, a silhouette crosses, sound bars pulse. One 0..1 timeline
    drives every child (segments live inside the keyframes), fed either by
    CSS animation-timeline: view() or by scroll-fx.js via --nf-progress.
    Reduced motion / mobile get the designed static end-state.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="nf-mech__track" data-nf-scrub>
    <div class="nf-mech__stage">
      <div class="nf-mech__inner apple-container">
        <div class="nf-window" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="nf-window__sky"></span>
          <span class="nf-window__glow"></span>

          {%- comment -%}
            Shadow story, scroll-driven: she reads by the window; a second
            silhouette walks in and stays — the home is not occupied by one
            lamp, but by people. Hand-drawn SVG silhouettes, blurred to read
            as shadows through a curtain.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            Reader: built from plain primitives (circle head, rounded-rect
            torso/limbs) instead of freehand curves, so the silhouette can't
            deform — a book held across the lap reads as a distinct wide
            shape breaking the torso's outline, arms taper down to it, and a
            small ponytail keeps the head from reading as perfectly round.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <svg class="nf-window__figure nf-window__figure--reader" viewBox="0 0 150 160" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <g fill="currentColor">
              <rect x="54" y="48" width="36" height="42" rx="16"/>
              <rect x="50" y="54" width="13" height="36" rx="6.5" transform="rotate(-16 57 54)"/>
              <rect x="87" y="54" width="13" height="36" rx="6.5" transform="rotate(16 93 54)"/>
              <rect x="50" y="98" width="18" height="18" rx="9"/>
              <rect x="52" y="112" width="14" height="46" rx="7"/>
              <rect x="76" y="98" width="18" height="18" rx="9"/>
              <rect x="78" y="112" width="14" height="46" rx="7" transform="rotate(7 85 114)"/>
              <rect x="36" y="82" width="72" height="20" rx="3" transform="rotate(-3 72 92)"/>
              <path d="M84,22 C94,26 97,42 90,56 C87,61 82,60 81,54 C86,44 85,32 78,24 Z"/>
              <g transform="rotate(8 72 44)">
                <rect x="63" y="40" width="18" height="16" rx="6"/>
                <circle cx="72" cy="28" r="16"/>
              </g>
            </g>
          </svg>

          {%- comment -%}
            Partner: same primitive technique — tapered torso, arms and legs
            mid-stride, so the walk-in reads as an actual person arriving,
            not a flat cutout sliding across the glass.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <svg class="nf-window__figure nf-window__figure--partner" viewBox="0 0 90 175" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <g fill="currentColor">
              <rect x="28" y="38" width="34" height="26" rx="13"/>
              <rect x="31" y="58" width="28" height="26" rx="13"/>
              <rect x="19" y="42" width="9" height="34" rx="4.5" transform="rotate(-16 23.5 42)"/>
              <rect x="62" y="42" width="9" height="34" rx="4.5" transform="rotate(20 66.5 42)"/>
              <rect x="32" y="80" width="14" height="34" rx="7" transform="rotate(10 39 80)"/>
              <rect x="35" y="110" width="12" height="38" rx="6" transform="rotate(16 41 112)"/>
              <rect x="44" y="80" width="14" height="34" rx="7" transform="rotate(-12 51 80)"/>
              <rect x="40" y="110" width="12" height="40" rx="6" transform="rotate(-6 46 112)"/>
              <rect x="38" y="28" width="14" height="12" rx="5"/>
              <circle cx="45" cy="18" r="13"/>
            </g>
          </svg>

          <span class="nf-window__frame"></span>
          <span class="nf-window__sill"></span>
          <div class="nf-soundbars">
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ol class="nf-mech__phases">
          <li class="nf-mech__phase nf-mech__phase--1">
            <h3 class="nf-mech__phase-title text-white">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_1_title != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_1_title }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_1_title' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </h3>
            <p class="body-standard text-muted-dark">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_1_body != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_1_body }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_1_body' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="nf-mech__phase nf-mech__phase--2">
            <h3 class="nf-mech__phase-title text-white">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_2_title != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_2_title }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_2_title' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </h3>
            <p class="body-standard text-muted-dark">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_2_body != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_2_body }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_2_body' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="nf-mech__phase nf-mech__phase--3">
            <h3 class="nf-mech__phase-title text-white">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_3_title != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_3_title }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_3_title' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </h3>
            <p class="body-standard text-muted-dark">
              {%- if section.settings.phase_3_body != blank -%}{{ section.settings.phase_3_body }}{%- else -%}{{ 'home.mechanism.phase_3_body' | t }}{%- endif -%}
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Mechanism",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Switch language at the top of the editor before editing text. Blank fields keep the built-in translation for that language."
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "overline", "label": "Overline" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "heading", "label": "Heading" },
    { "type": "textarea", "id": "subheading", "label": "Subheading" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "phase_1_title", "label": "Phase 1 title (light)" },
    { "type": "textarea", "id": "phase_1_body", "label": "Phase 1 body" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "phase_2_title", "label": "Phase 2 title (shadow)" },
    { "type": "textarea", "id": "phase_2_body", "label": "Phase 2 body" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "phase_3_title", "label": "Phase 3 title (sound)" },
    { "type": "textarea", "id": "phase_3_body", "label": "Phase 3 body" }
  ],
  "presets": [{ "name": "Mechanism" }]
}
{% endschema %}
